disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Get Excited!.

blurb.value: Jinx receives massively increased Movement Speed and stacking Attack Speed whenever she damages an enemy champion, tower, or inhibitor that is then killed or destroyed within 3 seconds.

description.value: Innate: Whenever an enemy champion, epic monster, turret or inhibitor dies within 3 seconds of being damaged by Jinx, she gains  175% bonus movement speed which decays over 6 seconds.

description2.value: Additionally, she gains  15% total attack speed and is allowed to exceed the attack speed cap for the same duration.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Jinx's attack speed cap is increased to 90.0 for the duration, however this value is already beyond the technical limit for attack speed. Jinx will get excited from killing a Rift Herald summoned by the enemy team with the Eye of the Herald as well.
notes.description: Displays additional information with effect table to the right.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Switcheroo!.

blurb.value: Jinx modifies her basic attacks by swapping between Pow-Pow, her minigun and Fishbones, her rocket launcher. Attacks with Pow-Pow grant Attack Speed, while attacks with Fishbones deal area of effect damage, gain increased range, and drain Mana.

description.value: Toggle: Jinx switches between Pow-Pow, her minigun, and Fishbones, her rocket launcher.

description2.value: Pow-Pow: Basic attacks with Pow-Pow grant her Rev'd up for 2.5 seconds, stacking up to 3 times. Rev'd up grants  bonus attack speed, with the first stack being twice as potent as the others. Stacks decay one at a time as they time-out.

description3.value: Fishbones: Basic attacks with Fishbones cost  mana on-attack to deal 110% AD modified physical damage to the main target as well as splash the damage to all enemies within a 150-radius area. The damage is affected by critical strike modifiers. While using Fishbones, Jinx gains  bonus range but loses  25% of her bonus attack speed.

description4.value: Attacks with Fishbones will not refresh the stack timer on Rev'd up and only the first attack after switching to it will benefit from Rev'd up's bonus attack speed.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Toggle abilities do not count as ability activations for the purposes of on-cast effects such as Spellblade, charging Spellbinder, and stacking Force Pulse. Jinx's first attack after switching to Fishbones can be triggered after 0.4 seconds, instead of using the attack timer. Despite Jinx starting the game using Pow-Pow she doesn't receive any bonus attack speed until Switcheroo! has been learned. Fishbones splash damage affects structures (minions will target Jinx) but does not affect targets if Jinx's attacks are blocked, dodged, or missed. With Runaan's Hurricane Pow-Pow generates one stack per enemy hit. Each of Runaan's Hurricane's additional bolts apply Fishbones' splash damage, which stacks with each other. Both weapons deal basic damage to their primary target (this includes the increased damage of Fishbones), which applies  life steal based on the damage dealt (post-mitigation) as usual. The splash damage of Fishbones is based on the pre-mitigation damage done to the primary target (which includes critical strikes), and is not considered modified physical damage. It deals default damage: It doesn't apply  life steal or on-hit effects. Damage for Fishbones: 110% AD (100% + 10%). Critical strike damage for Fishbones: 220% AD ((100% + 10%) × 2). Critical strike damage for Fishbones with Infinity Edge: 247.5% AD ((100% + 10%) × 2.25). Damage per Fishbones bolt: 44% AD ((100% + 10%) ×  0.4). Critical strike damage per Fishbones bolt: 88% AD (((100% + 10%) ×  0.4) × 2). Critical strike damage per Fishbones bolt with Infinity Edge: 99% AD (((100% + 10%) ×  0.4) × 2.25). Potential damage on stacked enemies with Fishbones and Runaan's Hurricane: 198% AD (110% + 44% + 44%). Potential critical strike damage on stacked enemies with Fishbones and Runaan's Hurricane: 396% AD (220% + 88% + 88%). Potential critical strike damage on stacked enemies with Fishbones, Runaan's Hurricane, and Infinity Edge: 445.5% AD ((247.5% + 99% + 99%)).

Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Flame Chompers!.

blurb.value: Jinx throws out a line of snare grenades that explode after 5 seconds, lighting enemies on fire. Flame Chompers will bite enemy champions who walk over them, rooting them in place.

description.value: Active: Jinx tosses out 3 Chompers at the target location perpendicular to her facing, which arm after 0.7 seconds and explode after 5 seconds, dealing magic damage over 1.5 seconds to all enemies within a small area.

leveling.value: Total Magic Damage:»70 / 120 / 170 / 220 / 270 (+ 100% AP)«Magic Damage per instance:23.33 / 40 / 56.67 / 73.33 / 90 (+ 33.3% AP)

description2.value: Chompers prematurely explode on contact with an enemy champion, knocking down and rooting them for 1.5 seconds. An enemy champion can only set off and be damaged by one Chomper.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Super Mega Death Rocket!.

effect radius.value: 400 / 1000 / 1000

width.value: 280

blurb.value: Jinx fires a super rocket across the map that gains damage as it travels. The rocket will explode upon colliding with an enemy champion, dealing damage to it and surrounding enemies based on their missing Health.

description.value: Active: Jinx fires a rocket in the target direction, granting brief sight of the area it flies through. The rocket explodes upon colliding with an enemy champion, dealing physical damage to the champion and all enemies in an area around them and revealing the area around them for 2 seconds.

description2.value: The rocket deals 10% − 100% (based on distance traveled) damage based on travel distance, the bonus damage based on missing health is retained.

leveling2.value: Max. Physical Damage:»250 / 300 / 350 / 400 / 450 (+ 150% bonus AD) (+ 25 / 27.5 / 30 / 32.5 / 35% of target's missing health)«Min. Physical Damage:25 / 30 / 35 / 40 / 45 (+ 15% bonus AD) (+ 25 / 27.5 / 30 / 32.5 / 35% of target's missing health)

description3.value: Enemies surrounding the main target take 80% damage. Bonus damage from missing health is based on each unit's own missing health.

leveling3.value: Max. Secondary Damage:»200 / 240 / 280 / 320 / 360 (+ 120% bonus AD) (+ 20 / 22 / 24 / 26 / 28% of target's missing health)«Min. Secondary Damage:20 / 24 / 28 / 32 / 36 (+ 12% bonus AD) (+ 20 / 22 / 24 / 26 / 28% of target's missing health)
